As depicted in Tables 1, 2, 3, the baseline methods pre-trained on synthetic medical images from RoentGen [18] exhibit comparable or superior performance relative to those pre-trained on real images. This finding suggests that a domain-specific generative model can yield synthetic image datasets rich in information, enabling VLP models to effectively learn visual representations.
